    "text": "Job Description\nThe Oncology department at Novartis Institutes for BioMedical Research (NIBR) is currently recruiting for a talented and motivated Scientific Associate to join the Biochemistry group.\nThe group is responsible for providing biochemistry/biophysics/enzymology expertise in early drug discovery and is fully integrated into the Disease Area Oncology, working in close collaboration with cell biologists, chemists, structural biologists and screening scientists to drive the identification and optimization of small molecule drugs.\nMajor Accountabilities\n Designing, developing and carrying out novel biochemical/biophysical assays (mainly enzymatic, binding or biophysical assays) using a wide range of technologies Characterizing mechanism of action for key compounds Contributing to functional characterization of proteins or protein mutants considered as potential drug targets (in close collaboration with the Target Identification and Validation group within Oncology) Data analysis, interpreting and detailed documenting of experiments according to company policies Presenting results to teams Maintaining laboratory instruments and workstations Depending on level of experience, serving as deputy for the Lab Head\nMinimum Requirements\nEducation: Master&#x2019;s degree (or equivalent) with good knowledge in Biochemistry/Biophysics/Enzymology and at least 3 years laboratory experience in a similar position in research (no PhD/PostDoc)\nLanguage: Fluency in English (oral and written) is essential. Knowledge of German or French would be beneficial\nAdditional\n Sound knowledge and hands-on expertise in biophysics (e.g. DSF, SPR, ITC, MS) and/or conventional assay technologies used for enzymatic of binding assays using fluorescence (e.g. FI, TR-FRET, FP) or luminescence (e.g. AlphaScreen) Experience with radioactive technologies (e.g. SPA, filtration assays) would be of advantage Some interest and skills in IT (MS Office, curve fitting software such as XLfit or GraphPad Prism) and lab automation systems (small laboratory workstations e.g. Biomek 4000) are required for efficient data evaluation and assay execution Ability to regularly adapt skills and knowledge to new targets and technologies An independent and well organized working style with an eye for detail and commitment to the highest quality standards An open and communicative approach, capable of collaborating successfully across organizational boundaries\nDivision\nNIBR\nBusiness Unit\nOncology NIBR\nCountry\nSwitzerland\nWork Location\nBasel\nCompany/Legal Entity\nNovartis Pharma AG\nFunctional Area\nResearch &amp; Development\nJob Type\nFull Time\nEmployment Type\nRegular"
